org.modelio.api.modelio.diagram

Enum LinkPointKind

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<LinkPointKind>
      • org.modelio.api.modelio.diagram.LinkPointKind
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<LinkPointKind>

    public enum LinkPointKind
extends java.lang.Enum<LinkPointKind>
    Kind of a ILinkPoint is one of the point that compose a link. Defines an anchor point at the connection extremities or a bend point.

    A bend point may be either automatic or fixed.

    • automatic points may be freely modified or deleted by the connection router,
    • fixed bend points will not move unless the connection route is not consistent.
    An anchor point may be a sliding or a fixed anchor:
    • anchors may be located anywhere on the node. They will often move to align with the adjacent bend point or the opposite anchor if none.
    • anchors are predefined anchors whose location is determined by the node. ILinkPoint.setLocation(Point) will not move the anchor. Instead it will select the nearest anchor from the requested location.
